</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A basic tension in securities regulati=
on is: Would you rather have something done=C2=A0<em>badly</em>, or <em>not=
 at all</em>? Or, since everything happens at the margin: Would you rather =
have=C2=A0<em>more=C2=A0</em>of the thing, at a lower average quality, or=
=C2=A0<em>less=C2=A0</em>of it at a higher average quality?</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">This comes up most classically in disclosure regulations f=
or public companies. Every time the US Securities and Exchange Commission w=
rites new rules saying that public companies have to disclose more about so=
mething, that (1) arguably improves the information available to investors =
about public companies but (2) arguably makes it harder and more expensive =
for companies to go public. There are <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
